<font color="#FF0000">NURSES WRITING &amp; POETRY</font><br>
<tt>Mon Feb  3 20:14:34 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To the author of &quot;God Bless the Nurses&quot; and others who want to share the nurses pain, read &quot;Visions of War, Dreams of Peace&quot; an anthology of women's poetry from the American war on Viet Nam, published by Warner Books, 1991, edited by Lynda Van Devanter and Joan Furey. Nurse Dusty is being modest, some of her writing is in that collection. I was there but the great spirit spared me from what the combat guys and nurses went through. Thank you to the women for healing us and setting an example for us guys to use in expressing ourselves. We may not be able to fully share your pain but want you to know that we have read your poems and stories and hope that knowledge helps break down your walls of isolation. <br><br>
Lewis Downey Army MARS AB8AAL Phu Loi '71-'72
